LOTTE ENTERTAINMENT PRESENTS

01:12.105 --> 01:14.881
HAN Hyo-joo

01:21.721 --> 01:24.600
<i>At a new construction site in Seoul yesterday...</i>
CHUN Woo-hee

01:24.724 --> 01:26.024
<i>an old album has been discovered.</i>

01:26.025 --> 01:28.403
<i>an old album has been discovered.</i>
YOO Yeon-seok

01:28.861 --> 01:32.741
<i>The album dates back to 1944.</i>

01:32.798 --> 01:38.373
<i>It's by a faceless singer,
SEO Yeon-hee, entitled...</i>

01:38.471 --> 01:39.848
<i>JOSEON'S HEART</i>

01:40.339 --> 01:43.047
<i>Look forward to it being restored soon.</i>

01:43.142 --> 01:45.952
<i>You're listening to Classic Oldies.</i>

01:46.946 --> 01:51.918
LOVE, LIES

01:56.989 --> 01:58.024
<i>SEO Yeon-hee...</i>

01:59.091 --> 01:59.758
DAESUNG ARTIST AGENCY

01:59.759 --> 02:02.527
<i>I first met her at the Agency which no longer exists.</i>
DAESUNG ARTIST AGENCY

02:02.528 --> 02:05.509
<i>I first met her at the Agency
which no longer exists.</i>

02:10.870 --> 02:12.144
Hello.

02:12.438 --> 02:15.749
One, two!

02:15.841 --> 02:20.483
<i>Though occupied by Japan,
restaurants flourished.</i>

02:20.579 --> 02:23.059
<i>And artists were needed.</i>

02:24.083 --> 02:28.031
<i>Agencies represented artists
to give performances.</i>

02:28.120 --> 02:32.569
<i>And some trained young girls
and raised them as artists.</i>

02:37.930 --> 02:42.930
<i>♪ The peony is the queen of flowers ♪</i>

02:55.114 --> 03:03.090
<i>♪ The sunflower is a loyal subject ♪</i>

03:03.155 --> 03:05.431
Ye-hyang is all booked up.

03:06.058 --> 03:07.059
Wol-son?

03:07.593 --> 03:09.869
Make note!

03:10.162 --> 03:11.163
Il-hyang?

03:12.031 --> 03:14.375
And Hang-a? Got it.

03:14.533 --> 03:15.273
Thanks!

03:15.401 --> 03:23.401
<i>♪ The apricot blossom is a child ♪</i>

03:23.609 --> 03:25.748
The song So-yool just sang...

03:26.011 --> 03:29.288
is the best of all traditional songs.

03:29.982 --> 03:31.689
It's difficult to sing.

03:32.117 --> 03:35.394
And demands the listener
to have noble ears.

03:35.888 --> 03:39.700
Historically, those with tasteful ears...

03:39.825 --> 03:45.104
have cherished this song
as the best of the best.

03:46.899 --> 03:49.311
All your mouth can do is yawn?

03:51.136 --> 03:53.742
Aren't you embarrassed before So-yool?

03:54.173 --> 03:56.153
Where are your manners?

04:09.188 --> 04:11.828
What did you eat to sing so well?

04:11.924 --> 04:12.924
Breast milk.

04:13.092 --> 04:15.766
Her mom was a master singer.

04:16.661 --> 04:19.267
It's just a few lousy coins!

04:19.697 --> 04:22.235
What's going on?

04:22.301 --> 04:24.969
Where were the clothes?

04:24.970 --> 04:26.881
It's your fault!

04:26.939 --> 04:30.318
Our girls couldn't work yesterday!

04:30.442 --> 04:31.921
So pay up!

04:31.977 --> 04:36.790
I put the clothes on his rickshaw
on time to get delivered!

04:37.016 --> 04:39.584
But the fool got lured into gambling...

04:39.585 --> 04:41.258
Fine! I'll pay!

04:41.387 --> 04:43.890
Bloody damn! It's just a few coins!

04:44.023 --> 04:46.594
Come here! Go!

04:46.725 --> 04:49.797
She grew without a mom.
She's good at chores.

04:50.029 --> 04:51.872
Take her for 10 coins.

04:51.931 --> 04:52.636
What?

04:52.765 --> 04:53.765
Fine!

04:54.967 --> 04:56.173
Let's say 5 coins.

04:56.802 --> 04:59.373
She'll pay off the rest by working.

04:59.605 --> 05:01.084
No, Dad!

05:01.140 --> 05:03.211
You have no choice!

05:03.275 --> 05:05.016
I don't need you.

05:09.081 --> 05:17.081
♪ The sailor sings in the distance ♪

05:17.423 --> 05:20.131
Like Madam LEE Nan-young too?

05:23.996 --> 05:26.340
You're the rickshaw driver's girl?

05:27.967 --> 05:29.913
What's your name?

05:37.109 --> 05:38.110
Tell me?

05:38.978 --> 05:40.651
SEO Yeon-hee. Why?

05:40.980 --> 05:42.926
I'm JUNG So-yool.

05:43.215 --> 05:45.456
We learn fun things here.

05:45.517 --> 05:49.055
Wanna learn too? I can ask Mother.

05:49.121 --> 05:50.759
You're an annoying girl.

05:53.025 --> 05:54.368
Let's learn together?

05:55.828 --> 05:58.434
<i>She was as sharp as a cactus flower.</i>

05:58.797 --> 06:01.300
<i>That's how we met.</i>

06:01.367 --> 06:04.405
<i>And we became the closest of friends.</i>

06:06.805 --> 06:09.513
We're graduating! I could fly!

06:09.742 --> 06:11.576
I won't get blue, will I?

06:11.577 --> 06:14.820
Of course you'll get red!
But I'm worried...

06:14.880 --> 06:16.723
If I get blue, I'll die!

06:16.782 --> 06:18.783
Silly! You won't get blue!

06:18.784 --> 06:21.765
Don't worry!
It'll be a pretty red one!

06:27.826 --> 06:29.772
- SEO Geum-hong!
- Yes?

06:31.196 --> 06:32.196
Congratulations.

06:32.231 --> 06:34.370
- KIM Ok-hyang!
- Yes.

06:37.703 --> 06:38.408
Congratulations.

06:38.470 --> 06:39.471
SEO Yeon-hee!

06:46.845 --> 06:50.793
Once you open the box,
you're no longer students.

06:50.849 --> 06:54.524
You're official artists
on Daesung's roster.

06:54.586 --> 06:58.090
Watch at all times
not to defame our agency.

06:58.157 --> 06:59.864
Yes, Mother.

07:00.392 --> 07:03.669
Now, open them.

07:14.373 --> 07:17.047
- I'm so happy!
- Congratulations.

07:30.122 --> 07:33.262
If you didn't get what you want...

07:35.260 --> 07:39.231
Devote yourselves to further
training as artists.

07:39.298 --> 07:41.972
- Understood?
- Yes, Mother.

07:46.805 --> 07:50.753
Reds and oranges will have
pictures taken for our booklet.

07:50.809 --> 07:53.478
Get ready and gather
by the pond.

07:53.479 --> 07:54.981
Yes, sir.

08:01.620 --> 08:04.328
- I told you.
- I'm so happy!

08:05.157 --> 08:05.965
What about us?

08:06.024 --> 08:07.225
What about you?

08:07.226 --> 08:09.103
We don't get pictures taken?

08:09.161 --> 08:11.038
You're blues!

08:11.096 --> 08:14.077
You mean we're courtesans?

08:14.133 --> 08:14.873
Yes.

08:15.000 --> 08:19.107
We didn't train hard for 4 years
to be prostitutes!

08:20.105 --> 08:22.085
You must remember.

08:23.108 --> 08:26.749
You are flowers that understand words.

08:28.013 --> 08:32.962
Not only understand what people say...

08:34.620 --> 08:39.091
but it means you know
literature and the arts.

08:40.659 --> 08:42.501
Though of low status...

08:42.861 --> 08:45.535
if you become skilled artists...

08:45.898 --> 08:49.641
high officials will open
their eyes and ears...

08:50.335 --> 08:54.283
and you'll bloom as
flowers that cannot be plucked.

08:54.606 --> 08:57.917
Sell your talent, smiles, or bodies...

08:58.143 --> 08:59.377
What's most important?

08:59.378 --> 09:02.689
That you sell! Then what should you gain?

09:02.781 --> 09:03.384
Guess.

09:03.549 --> 09:04.549
Rice?

09:05.651 --> 09:08.291
Food is not everything. Wrong!

09:09.321 --> 09:10.321
Clothes?

09:10.355 --> 09:12.892
That's why you're a courtesan.

09:14.026 --> 09:18.406
You'll have all the rice
and clothes with this!

09:18.497 --> 09:20.204
What is it, you ask?

09:23.335 --> 09:24.837
A man's heart.

09:25.504 --> 09:28.451
<i>Nothing is more foolish
than trusting a man.</i>

09:28.507 --> 09:32.455
<i>Though you go out and dance
and sing for them...</i>

09:32.744 --> 09:36.658
<i>your performances are not just for them.</i>

09:36.782 --> 09:39.524
Then where is a man's heart?

09:39.585 --> 09:40.585
Here?

09:42.187 --> 09:43.393
Or here?

09:44.556 --> 09:45.694
No.

09:46.792 --> 09:47.793
Right...

09:51.296 --> 09:52.296
Here!

09:53.265 --> 09:56.269
Be proud and gain men's hearts!

09:57.236 --> 09:59.910
It means we're whores!

10:02.174 --> 10:05.121
One, two...

10:05.444 --> 10:06.444
Three!

10:06.511 --> 10:09.424
Remember girls.
1944, DAESUNG AGENCY GRADUATION

10:10.182 --> 10:12.253
You are artists.

10:19.691 --> 10:22.035
- <i>Born and raised in the agency...</i>
- Daesung booklet!

10:22.427 --> 10:25.374
<i>I knew nothing of the world outside.</i>

10:26.398 --> 10:31.905
<i>I just practiced singing
traditional songs everyday.</i>

10:32.571 --> 10:36.519
<i>But the age of traditional artists
was coming to an end.</i>

10:36.575 --> 10:39.613
<i>The country was astir with modern songs.</i>

10:39.678 --> 10:43.057
<i>Yeon-hee and I were also drawn by them.</i>

10:43.415 --> 10:45.554
It's Madam LEE Nan-young.

10:46.351 --> 10:49.491
It's really her.

10:50.122 --> 10:55.595
<i>♪ Seep into my heart ♪</i>

10:55.661 --> 11:02.010
<i>♪ The bride by the port ♪</i>

11:02.134 --> 11:08.483
<i>♪ Her clothes soaked with tears ♪</i>

11:15.714 --> 11:17.581
Hello, San-wol.

11:17.582 --> 11:20.529
Thank you for coming. Shall we?

11:22.587 --> 11:25.329
Let's see the girls.

11:26.158 --> 11:28.604
Daesung's booklet of artists.

11:50.682 --> 11:52.855
She must be Cho-hyang's daughter.

11:53.085 --> 11:56.066
I heard men are infatuated by her.

11:57.289 --> 11:59.269
Like mother like daughter.

12:00.726 --> 12:03.036
Allow me to serve you tonight.

12:32.257 --> 12:34.392
How'd you spend your first pay?

12:34.393 --> 12:37.670
Well... Nothing much.

12:42.567 --> 12:44.569
Gave it all to your dad?

12:46.705 --> 12:48.685
I knew you would.

12:50.809 --> 12:51.810
Tada!

12:53.378 --> 12:54.378
What's this?

12:54.479 --> 12:55.479
A gift!

12:56.114 --> 12:57.114
Open it.

12:59.050 --> 13:01.826
<i>LEE NAN-YOUNG</i>

13:02.320 --> 13:04.596
You wanted it.

13:09.494 --> 13:11.337
Don't cry!

13:11.463 --> 13:16.913
But I didn't get anything for you.

13:18.537 --> 13:20.414
So-yool...

13:22.541 --> 13:25.647
You're my one and only bosom friend.

13:25.710 --> 13:26.882
Thanks.

13:55.073 --> 13:57.280
I have to go out for a second.

13:57.476 --> 13:58.682
Where?

14:23.802 --> 14:25.577
What do you think?

14:25.804 --> 14:26.804
About what?

14:26.805 --> 14:27.977
That lady.

14:28.607 --> 14:29.745
How does she look?

14:29.908 --> 14:31.080
Well...

14:34.079 --> 14:39.791
She's the best of all
the pictures you've sent so far.

14:39.918 --> 14:40.918
Really?

14:41.953 --> 14:43.455
Let's see.

14:44.756 --> 14:49.296
With sparkling eyes and neat attire...

14:49.794 --> 14:52.798
she must have the heart of an angel.

14:54.299 --> 14:56.467
But her mouth...

14:56.468 --> 14:59.972
What about the mouth?

15:00.205 --> 15:01.775
Talking back!

15:01.840 --> 15:03.547
Looks like she'll be stubborn.

15:03.608 --> 15:04.808
I am not!

15:04.809 --> 15:05.809
See!

15:06.444 --> 15:08.549
Must be stubborn.

15:12.150 --> 15:17.259
In my eyes, no one can be more beautiful.

15:22.093 --> 15:23.766
But your mother...

15:24.896 --> 15:28.639
She'll never allow you to marry an artist.

15:33.905 --> 15:35.043
So-yool.

15:35.707 --> 15:37.618
You know me.

15:38.209 --> 15:39.984
I'm modern!

15:40.045 --> 15:42.212
Mom can't control me.

15:42.213 --> 15:44.215
I'm a wild and free spirit!

15:51.323 --> 15:52.734
Silly.

15:55.126 --> 16:00.371
2 years should do to be my bride.

16:06.204 --> 16:08.206
Who said I'll marry...

16:11.776 --> 16:13.756
It's Madam LEE Nan-young!

16:19.417 --> 16:20.725
'Madam'?

16:22.621 --> 16:27.263
I'm surprised you know her
and even call her 'Madam'.

16:27.459 --> 16:30.963
Who doesn't know her in Joseon?

16:31.663 --> 16:33.472
You've heard her songs too?

16:33.531 --> 16:36.205
Of course! I love her songs.

16:36.401 --> 16:39.280
I'm dying to meet her someday.

16:39.938 --> 16:40.678
Then...

16:40.739 --> 16:41.740
SPRING DREAM

16:41.840 --> 16:43.707
Have you heard this song?

16:43.708 --> 16:46.188
Of course! It's my favorite!

16:46.711 --> 16:49.282
Written and composed by CHOI Chi-rim.

16:49.748 --> 16:51.250
Don't know this song?

17:18.242 --> 17:20.655
Where were you!

17:20.712 --> 17:22.714
Everyone's looking for you!

17:25.717 --> 17:27.390
Say hello, Yeon-hee.

17:27.452 --> 17:30.365
This is KIM Yoon-woo.

17:30.922 --> 17:32.128
And this is...

17:32.257 --> 17:35.261
my best friend, SEO Yeon-hee.

17:37.095 --> 17:38.096
Nice to meet you.

17:38.797 --> 17:39.935
Hello.

17:44.569 --> 17:46.515
How've you been, ma'am?

17:46.705 --> 17:48.013
It's been a while.

17:48.973 --> 17:50.350
When did you return?

17:50.742 --> 17:53.416
I came back for good today.

17:53.545 --> 17:55.752
Then you should've gone to your mom.

17:55.814 --> 18:01.662
You're still as beautiful
as a flower in the snow.

18:01.920 --> 18:02.955
Come with me.

18:04.355 --> 18:05.766
Yes, Mother.

18:09.494 --> 18:11.997
Please don't scold So-yool!

18:12.230 --> 18:14.767
I cajoled her to stay with me!

18:27.879 --> 18:28.879
Yes.

18:31.182 --> 18:32.752
At 6 PM?

18:35.453 --> 18:37.763
Thank you, councilor.

18:38.790 --> 18:40.792
I'm indebted to you.

18:41.192 --> 18:42.192
Goodbye.

18:48.633 --> 18:50.613
- Tonight...
- At 6 o'clock?

18:51.035 --> 18:53.345
- Get So-yool...
- Ready!

19:31.543 --> 19:32.843
It's a car!

19:32.844 --> 19:33.845
Get in.

19:34.879 --> 19:38.156
I can't. I have a performance soon.

19:38.216 --> 19:41.163
You'll regret it if you don't.

19:41.853 --> 19:42.888
But I can't.

19:44.088 --> 19:46.227
It's an important performance.

19:46.291 --> 19:47.827
What time is it at?

19:48.226 --> 19:49.226
6 o'clock.

19:50.795 --> 19:54.299
I'll bring you back here by 5 PM!

19:56.134 --> 19:57.134
Okay?

19:58.369 --> 20:01.350
- Whose car is this?
- A friend's.

20:01.606 --> 20:03.882
- Where are we going?
- To meet a friend.

20:04.442 --> 20:06.388
- Where?
- A friend's house.

20:07.412 --> 20:08.823
Hey!

20:16.855 --> 20:19.699
- Where is this?
- A friend's house.

20:27.866 --> 20:30.608
Madam LEE Nan-young?

20:35.440 --> 20:36.907
Uncomfortable with me?

20:36.908 --> 20:37.978
No!

20:38.576 --> 20:40.522
Of course not!

20:41.079 --> 20:44.822
I really respect you, madam.

20:49.921 --> 20:50.921
So-yool?

20:50.955 --> 20:53.629
I'm just a pop music singer.

20:53.925 --> 20:58.135
I should respect you.
You're a master traditional singer.

20:58.363 --> 21:02.072
Oh no! Please...

21:02.967 --> 21:04.412
My singing is still...

21:04.969 --> 21:07.142
What a pretty darling?

21:07.238 --> 21:08.649
Like peach blossom?

21:08.706 --> 21:11.744
Right! Peach blossom.

21:11.910 --> 21:14.083
Title, 'Peach Blossom'!

21:14.679 --> 21:17.159
The song will be about you.

21:17.382 --> 21:20.920
His muse was you, So-yool?
I'm not surprised.

21:20.985 --> 21:23.693
I love all the songs he made.

21:25.156 --> 21:26.156
Songs?

21:26.457 --> 21:27.663
You didn't know?

21:28.126 --> 21:31.505
He was famous even while in Japan.

21:32.697 --> 21:34.643
Don't tell my mom.

21:35.133 --> 21:38.171
He wrote one of my songs
too, 'Spring Dream'.

21:40.171 --> 21:42.515
'Spring Dream'?

21:43.207 --> 21:46.176
- That's made by CHOI Chi-rim.
- Right!

21:46.177 --> 21:48.919
That's Mr. KIM's alias.

21:54.652 --> 21:58.532
If I tell you who I'm with,
you'll be shocked!

21:58.823 --> 22:00.166
Can you come now?

22:00.458 --> 22:01.458
Now?

22:06.431 --> 22:10.267
Thank you for agreeing to
my sudden request.

22:10.268 --> 22:14.876
Why of course! I always welcome my fans.

22:14.939 --> 22:18.944
Will you do me a favor in return?

22:19.477 --> 22:21.678
Of course! Anything.

22:21.679 --> 22:23.818
Sing me a traditional song?

22:24.082 --> 22:26.153
Oh please.

22:26.217 --> 22:28.163
I love traditional songs.

22:28.219 --> 22:30.995
Could you sing for me?

22:32.323 --> 22:37.323
<i>♪ A minute seems... ♪</i>

22:49.507 --> 22:55.185
<i>♪ Like a lifetime ♪</i>

22:56.614 --> 22:58.218
How can you be so senseless?

22:58.282 --> 23:00.283
Have you lost your mind?

23:00.284 --> 23:04.232
I thought you were quietly
getting ready in your room!

23:04.288 --> 23:08.065
You have to get your hair and makeup done!

23:08.159 --> 23:09.194
What time is it?

23:09.260 --> 23:12.173
Damn! I forgot my watch.

23:18.236 --> 23:19.579
You stay here.

23:19.904 --> 23:22.748
What? I don't want to stay alone.

23:22.807 --> 23:25.686
Take care of Yeon-hee.

23:26.210 --> 23:27.210
Sure.

23:29.380 --> 23:30.415
Let's.

23:32.016 --> 23:33.016
Take care!

23:42.527 --> 23:44.905
- Go inside.
- What?

23:45.163 --> 23:47.370
You're a fan, right? Go in.

24:10.521 --> 24:13.297
Japanese police commissioner,
Hirata Kiyoshi.

24:13.925 --> 24:18.999
He's famous for being cruel,
but has an appreciation for the arts.

24:22.200 --> 24:25.374
You must gain his heart.

25:02.373 --> 25:07.373
<i>♪ One smile ♪</i>

25:20.091 --> 25:25.091
<i>♪ Makes a hundred coquetry ♪</i>

25:47.652 --> 25:49.393
Come pour him a drink.

25:53.891 --> 25:55.370
Did you enjoy it, sir?

25:56.627 --> 25:57.627
Yes.

25:58.095 --> 26:01.440
Her mother was a famous master singer too.

26:16.514 --> 26:18.994
Joseon's traditional song?

26:19.584 --> 26:21.757
It's called, 'Ujo Pyeonggeo', sir.

26:22.787 --> 26:24.767
Do you know Japan's 'Joruri'?

26:25.623 --> 26:28.570
I've heard the 'Yokyoku'...

26:29.260 --> 26:30.933
But 'Joruri' is uncommon.

26:31.429 --> 26:36.139
It'd be an honor to hear it some day.

26:43.374 --> 26:44.375
This way.

26:53.050 --> 26:56.429
After your bath, change into this.

27:00.391 --> 27:03.133
You have an appreciation for the arts.

27:03.794 --> 27:06.741
And you think dearly of artists.

27:07.865 --> 27:13.315
So I humbly performed for you.

27:16.941 --> 27:19.444
That is all I have to offer, sir.

27:20.444 --> 27:22.720
I didn't prepare for anything else.

27:40.498 --> 27:46.744
You said artists are flowers
that can't be plucked.

27:46.837 --> 27:52.287
Do you know why artists are called flowers?

27:54.845 --> 27:57.849
Flowers get plucked and put in vases.

27:58.215 --> 28:01.253
They are for getting plucked
by men who want them.

28:02.086 --> 28:04.066
That is an artist!

28:06.324 --> 28:12.900
Then I'm basically a prostitute?

28:15.499 --> 28:20.107
How dare you say that!

28:32.350 --> 28:33.988
What are you doing here?

28:35.619 --> 28:36.757
Honey!

28:37.988 --> 28:41.993
I waited all last night.
What took you so long?

28:43.094 --> 28:44.198
It's nothing.

28:45.830 --> 28:47.241
I'm hungry.

28:51.702 --> 28:55.514
What about school?
You're really going to quit?

28:56.474 --> 28:58.954
I already quit a long time ago.

28:59.510 --> 29:02.787
Your mother will be disappointed.

29:03.914 --> 29:06.292
There's no end to Mom's greed.

29:06.784 --> 29:10.527
She wouldn't be satisfied even
if I become Governor-General.

29:15.659 --> 29:16.659
So-yool.

29:17.361 --> 29:22.333
In a world like this,
being successful is a sin.

29:23.100 --> 29:27.640
As you go up the ladder,
you trample on our people.

29:28.239 --> 29:35.453
Isn't it better to make songs
that comfort this country?

29:41.552 --> 29:45.295
Promise you'll sing my song?

29:46.257 --> 29:48.794
I can't be a pop singer.

29:48.959 --> 29:51.795
Think pop music is lowly?

29:51.796 --> 29:55.073
Of course I don't.

29:56.634 --> 29:59.240
I just love traditional songs.

29:59.537 --> 30:01.039
But So-yool...

30:01.672 --> 30:08.112
Think even one person there
will ever get to hear you sing?

30:08.212 --> 30:11.557
They don't have the right
or the ears to hear it?

30:11.882 --> 30:12.883
Fine.

30:13.317 --> 30:16.093
Maybe your Mother is right.

30:17.221 --> 30:22.068
But they don't need songs
to idly appreciate.

30:22.193 --> 30:26.972
What they need
are tears and laughter.

30:27.498 --> 30:31.469
I'm going to make
a national song of our time.

30:32.636 --> 30:35.845
A song for the tired
and weary hearts of Joseon.

30:36.674 --> 30:41.680
A song made complete
when sung by the people.

30:48.252 --> 30:49.253
I forgot.

31:05.169 --> 31:07.615
Madam LEE Nan-young's concert?

31:08.606 --> 31:11.450
She especially invited you.

31:12.977 --> 31:15.048
I'll go with Yeon-hee.

31:15.613 --> 31:17.183
Thank you so much!

31:22.219 --> 31:23.254
I'll go.

31:28.526 --> 31:29.698
Yoon-woo!

31:33.130 --> 31:36.373
I love traditional songs.

31:37.101 --> 31:40.275
But I really want to sing your song.

31:43.240 --> 31:47.689
And if I could...

31:52.216 --> 31:55.891
I want to be Joseon's heart.

32:26.684 --> 32:31.190
<i>♪ How much longer? ♪</i>

32:31.255 --> 32:35.931
<i>♪ No, no! Not tonight ♪</i>

32:39.263 --> 32:43.234
Encore! Encore!

32:43.300 --> 32:44.540
Thank you everyone.

32:44.635 --> 32:48.378
I feel like I could sing all night.

32:48.439 --> 32:52.945
And I'm so happy to share my songs
with my special guests.

32:53.277 --> 32:57.817
A few days ago,
I happened to hear a lady sing.

32:58.415 --> 33:01.225
It was literally music to my ears.

33:01.585 --> 33:03.319
It was so good...

33:03.320 --> 33:05.266
I couldn't sleep all night.

33:05.689 --> 33:10.035
Music can touch and stir people's souls.

33:11.595 --> 33:14.838
She made me realize
the joy of singing again.

33:16.367 --> 33:18.210
And she's here tonight.

33:20.671 --> 33:22.480
Will you sing for us?

33:23.707 --> 33:25.618
Let's give her a big welcome!

33:25.676 --> 33:26.676
Hey!

33:28.112 --> 33:29.489
Ms. SEO Yeon-hee!

33:43.160 --> 33:44.571
Go on up.

33:45.729 --> 33:46.730
Hurry.

34:01.278 --> 34:04.614
Written and composed by
CHOI Chi-rim.

34:04.615 --> 34:05.787
'Spring Dream'!

34:16.827 --> 34:22.777
<i>♪ Spring wind is blowing everywhere ♪</i>

34:22.833 --> 34:27.833
<i>♪ Azaleas are blooming ♪
♪ Spring is here ♪</i>

34:28.839 --> 34:34.687
<i>♪ On the country girl's lovely back ♪</i>

34:34.812 --> 34:42.812
<i>♪ The bent water-carrying yoke ♪
♪ feels light ♪</i>

34:46.889 --> 34:52.362
<i>♪ The spring wind blows ♪
♪ in the south ♪</i>

34:52.896 --> 35:00.838
<i>♪ How lovely the azaleas ♪
♪ blooming again ♪</i>

35:00.904 --> 35:03.851
<i>♪ I'm so happy ♪</i>

35:03.907 --> 35:08.907
<i>♪ I'll go out to meet ♪
♪ my love on his way to me ♪</i>

35:09.680 --> 35:14.493
<i>♪ What if we miss each other? ♪</i>

35:14.551 --> 35:20.263
<i>♪ And pass by ♪</i>

35:34.037 --> 35:36.347
<i>Let's give her a big welcome!</i>

35:37.775 --> 35:38.947
<i>Ms. SEO Yeon-hee!</i>

36:01.865 --> 36:02.865
Here.

36:07.371 --> 36:08.371
Have a seat.

36:15.946 --> 36:17.425
Yeon-hee!

36:23.053 --> 36:24.259
Did you go somewhere?

36:24.655 --> 36:25.895
Yes.

36:28.959 --> 36:31.599
About your boyfriend...

36:32.629 --> 36:33.869
Yoon-woo?

36:33.964 --> 36:34.964
Yes.

36:35.699 --> 36:38.873
He's a bit strange.

36:39.369 --> 36:41.280
He asked me to make an album.

36:42.806 --> 36:45.650
- He asked you?
- Yes.

36:45.809 --> 36:49.382
He said he's CHOI Chi-rim,
who wrote 'Spring Dream'.

36:51.281 --> 36:52.624
What did you say?

36:53.750 --> 36:54.421
What?

36:54.484 --> 36:57.465
Did you say you'll do it?

37:01.825 --> 37:03.827
It's true?

37:05.028 --> 37:07.975
I found an amazing singer.

37:08.765 --> 37:10.867
But she won't make an album.

37:10.868 --> 37:14.441
Why? Who doesn't want to?
Did you say I'll produce it?

37:14.504 --> 37:18.646
She said no before I could explain.

37:19.443 --> 37:22.185
She is so stubborn.

37:22.880 --> 37:23.881
Man...

37:24.047 --> 37:27.153
Women are all the same. They only see me!

37:28.151 --> 37:30.097
See? There.

37:43.934 --> 37:44.934
Mister...

37:45.502 --> 37:47.345
CHOI Chi-rim?

37:53.010 --> 37:54.045
Here?

37:55.979 --> 37:56.979
Yes.

37:57.147 --> 37:58.854
Know 'Hymn of Death'?

38:11.328 --> 38:15.708
<i>♪ In the vast wilderness ♪</i>

38:16.199 --> 38:20.579
<i>♪ My life runs ♪</i>

38:21.271 --> 38:25.651
<i>♪ I dream of meeting you ♪</i>

38:26.243 --> 38:30.783
<i>♪ Wherever are you? ♪</i>

38:31.214 --> 38:35.663
<i>♪ In this lonely world ♪</i>

38:36.086 --> 38:41.160
<i>♪ This bitter human world ♪</i>

38:41.224 --> 38:46.224
<i>♪ What are you looking for? ♪</i>

38:54.771 --> 38:56.011
You can go.

39:10.921 --> 39:12.923
Come back in the morning.

39:19.596 --> 39:22.008
Still undecided?

39:23.400 --> 39:26.040
But I'm the top songwriter in Joseon!

39:26.103 --> 39:28.310
KIM Yoon-woo! No, CHOI Chi-rim!

39:28.672 --> 39:31.653
To make an album,
I'll have to leave Daesung.

39:31.808 --> 39:33.082
That's the reason?

39:33.143 --> 39:37.091
You'll make more money with the album.

39:37.314 --> 39:40.818
It's not that.
So-yool and I made a promise.

39:41.385 --> 39:44.628
To keep the honor
and live as artists for life.

39:45.055 --> 39:47.501
What damn honor of artists?

39:47.824 --> 39:49.826
So-yool and I are artists.

39:51.428 --> 39:53.101
Don't insult us.

39:55.298 --> 39:57.141
Look, Ms. SEO.

40:01.671 --> 40:04.311
How can an artist's son insult an artist?

40:06.543 --> 40:08.250
I'm not slighting artists.

40:09.613 --> 40:11.559
But artists' performances...

40:12.349 --> 40:16.024
are for gluttons who waste
money on a night of drinks.

40:17.854 --> 40:20.232
Whether you like it or not...

40:21.992 --> 40:24.302
your voice belongs to...

40:25.829 --> 40:29.504
the merchants, rickshaw drivers,
and even beggars.

40:31.868 --> 40:35.839
A voice that should belong to everyone!

40:38.775 --> 40:41.187
That's what must be Joseon's heart.

40:44.648 --> 40:46.559
Should it not?

41:17.714 --> 41:22.857
I must become a singer.

41:28.225 --> 41:30.205
Mr. KIM explained.

41:32.095 --> 41:37.067
That my voice must be Joseon's heart.

41:42.339 --> 41:43.477
So-yool!

41:44.207 --> 41:45.481
So-yool!

42:13.737 --> 42:14.738
So-yool?

42:14.804 --> 42:17.307
Why is it Yeon-hee and not me?

42:20.110 --> 42:20.781
Come inside.

42:20.844 --> 42:22.790
Why Yeon-hee?

42:23.380 --> 42:24.450
I'm sorry.

42:26.349 --> 42:31.059
But I need Yeon-hee for my song.

42:33.490 --> 42:34.992
Come in.

42:37.127 --> 42:38.128
So-yool.

42:43.900 --> 42:45.470
It's because...

42:45.702 --> 42:48.649
you didn't hear me sing.

42:49.005 --> 42:50.985
I only sang traditional songs.

42:51.141 --> 42:54.088
Madam LEE and you didn't hear me sing.

42:58.815 --> 43:04.265
<i>♪ Spring wind is blowing everywhere ♪</i>

43:04.354 --> 43:09.827
<i>♪ Azaleas are blooming ♪
♪ Spring is here ♪</i>

43:09.893 --> 43:15.070
<i>♪ On the country girl's lovely back ♪</i>

43:16.800 --> 43:18.336
<i>♪ The bent... ♪</i>

43:23.340 --> 43:25.149
How about this song?

43:25.242 --> 43:30.242
<i>♪ The sailor sings in the distance ♪</i>

43:40.790 --> 43:43.361
<i>♪ The waves... ♪</i>

43:50.100 --> 43:51.135
Listen.

43:52.936 --> 43:54.506
Until now...

43:56.106 --> 44:01.112
I've never had anyone in my heart but you.

44:02.345 --> 44:03.983
It'll always be you.

44:06.283 --> 44:09.389
My love won't change. Okay?

44:12.322 --> 44:13.665
I know.

44:13.723 --> 44:15.930
Then why are you crying?

44:17.060 --> 44:22.009
Because... I want to sing your song too.

44:27.737 --> 44:34.313
Then sing! I'll make all
the songs you want.

44:34.544 --> 44:38.117
I'll make a hundred songs for you!

45:08.912 --> 45:10.892
Perhaps for you...

45:11.081 --> 45:13.721
pop songs suit your level.

45:16.619 --> 45:19.065
Know why they're pop songs?

45:20.023 --> 45:24.995
Because they fade away in time.

45:27.597 --> 45:33.013
Remember that once you leave,
you cannot come back.

46:49.712 --> 46:53.319
Why don't you try writing the lyrics?

46:53.783 --> 46:55.729
How could I?

46:57.153 --> 46:59.224
Just be sincere.

46:59.889 --> 47:01.869
That's most important.

47:02.492 --> 47:03.493
Okay?

47:04.227 --> 47:05.365
Okay.

47:05.595 --> 47:06.596
Great!

47:08.131 --> 47:09.735
Are you okay?

47:13.670 --> 47:17.706
<i>♪ Now become the storm ♪</i>

47:17.707 --> 47:22.707
<i>♪ And awaken the sky ♪
♪ with its eyes closed ♪</i>

47:38.995 --> 47:40.201
Okay!

47:40.930 --> 47:44.275
Yeon-hee is amazing! It sounds good.

47:47.303 --> 47:48.748
You came?

47:54.677 --> 47:57.783
I think the second last one sounded best.

47:59.082 --> 48:00.720
What do you think?

48:00.884 --> 48:03.831
I think the second one
sounded really pretty.

48:05.488 --> 48:06.558
Yeon-hee?

48:06.623 --> 48:11.623
I liked the last one.
I felt most comfortable.

48:11.728 --> 48:15.301
It sounds a bit heavy.

48:15.932 --> 48:19.744
Like the song demands to feel something.

48:20.470 --> 48:22.882
- What about you?
- I love food.

48:26.342 --> 48:28.322
Give it your all!

48:28.778 --> 48:29.654
Okay?

48:29.779 --> 48:30.780
Ready?

49:31.274 --> 49:32.275
TWO MONTHS LATER

49:32.342 --> 49:34.788
Joong-sun and Jung-wol!

49:34.911 --> 49:37.482
Chae-sung and Bok-hyang!

49:37.547 --> 49:39.652
You four get ready now.

49:41.751 --> 49:43.285
Stop! Don't come!

49:43.286 --> 49:45.197
What about me?

49:45.355 --> 49:47.489
Wait! Hold on!

49:47.490 --> 49:48.490
She's so aggressive.

49:48.491 --> 49:50.525
What about Asawon?

49:50.526 --> 49:52.301
They won't take us either?

49:53.262 --> 49:55.640
I'm doomed.

49:55.698 --> 49:58.645
I have to pay my brother's tuition.

50:03.306 --> 50:04.580
Stop please!

50:07.644 --> 50:08.679
So-yool!

50:09.579 --> 50:10.579
You...

50:10.813 --> 50:11.951
Your hair!

50:12.949 --> 50:14.485
Weird, isn't it?

50:15.385 --> 50:16.989
I'm not used to it.

50:17.053 --> 50:20.626
It looks great! You look like a singer.

50:22.725 --> 50:24.727
I was worried I'd miss you.

50:30.133 --> 50:33.137
It's released? Congratulations!

50:33.336 --> 50:35.475
Not officially yet.

50:35.571 --> 50:37.847
We made 20 for censorship.

50:37.907 --> 50:40.649
- I had to give you one.
- Thanks.

50:40.710 --> 50:42.212
Let's listen to it now.

50:42.311 --> 50:44.450
Wait, So-yool.

50:47.016 --> 50:50.327
The band and the dancers
are waiting for me.

50:50.687 --> 50:52.860
There's a concert
before the release.

50:53.756 --> 50:56.498
I see. Then go on.

50:57.727 --> 50:58.728
Bye.

51:04.467 --> 51:07.744
There are tickets inside.
Come to the concert?

51:08.171 --> 51:09.343
Of course.

51:33.930 --> 51:36.934
SEO YEON-HEE

51:39.836 --> 51:43.807
TO MY BEST FRIEND IN THE
WORLD, JUNG SO-YOOL

51:44.674 --> 51:46.950
JOSEON'S HEART

51:52.949 --> 51:57.949
<i>♪ Should I trust my youth? ♪</i>

51:57.954 --> 52:01.925
<i>♪ Don't go! O night of youth! ♪</i>

52:37.260 --> 52:40.173
Yeon-hee! You have to change!

53:10.893 --> 53:18.505
<i>♪ Alone on a barren field ♪</i>

53:19.335 --> 53:23.306
<i>♪ With nowhere to lean ♪</i>

53:23.940 --> 53:28.218
<i>♪ Stands so lonely ♪</i>

53:28.945 --> 53:33.360
<i>♪ An unbloomed flower ♪</i>

53:33.950 --> 53:38.228
<i>♪ In the long darkness ♪</i>

53:38.821 --> 53:43.065
<i>♪ The sun does not rise ♪</i>

53:43.793 --> 53:47.707
<i>♪ In the hard, toiling days ♪</i>

53:48.764 --> 53:52.541
<i>♪ Only tears flow ♪</i>

53:53.870 --> 54:01.755
<i>♪ Tears, become the rain ♪</i>

54:03.779 --> 54:11.779
<i>♪ And soak our sad hearts ♪</i>

54:13.356 --> 54:18.738
<i>♪ Oh silence ♪</i>

54:18.961 --> 54:22.932
<i>♪ Now become thunder ♪</i>

54:22.999 --> 54:27.999
<i>♪ And shake the hushed land ♪</i>

54:34.176 --> 54:37.953
<i>♪ Oh sorrow ♪</i>

54:38.047 --> 54:42.052
<i>♪ Now become the storm ♪</i>

54:42.985 --> 54:47.985
<i>♪ And awaken the sky ♪
♪ with its eyes closed ♪</i>

54:59.702 --> 55:02.205
<i>Yeon-hee, the cactus flower...</i>

55:03.739 --> 55:08.654
<i>She is beating out the thorns on stage.</i>

55:09.879 --> 55:17.093
<i>♪ Tears, become the rain ♪</i>

55:19.288 --> 55:24.288
<i>♪ And soak our sad hearts ♪</i>

55:29.098 --> 55:34.980
<i>♪ Oh silence ♪</i>

55:35.037 --> 55:39.008
<i>♪ Now become thunder ♪</i>

55:39.075 --> 55:44.075
<i>♪ And shake the hushed land ♪</i>

55:50.086 --> 55:54.466
<i>♪ Oh sorrow ♪</i>

55:54.523 --> 55:58.699
<i>♪ Now become the storm ♪</i>

55:58.761 --> 56:03.761
<i>♪ And awaken the sky ♪
♪ with its eyes closed ♪</i>

56:38.467 --> 56:40.242
What did you think?

56:40.302 --> 56:43.511
Great! She'll be the next LEE Nan-young.

56:43.572 --> 56:45.874
I told you, didn't I?

56:45.875 --> 56:48.321
- She'll be a hit!
- Thank you!

56:50.613 --> 56:51.921
So-yool?

56:55.451 --> 56:56.794
You came.

56:57.153 --> 56:58.928
- Saw the concert?
- No!

57:04.326 --> 57:07.000
I waited for you to invite me.

57:09.532 --> 57:12.445
How could you not?

57:16.105 --> 57:17.550
Don't do it again.

57:18.507 --> 57:19.577
Let's go.

57:29.318 --> 57:32.322
Everyone! Raise your glasses.

57:32.388 --> 57:34.959
How about a toast to 'Joseon's Heart'?

57:35.024 --> 57:36.799
To 'Joseon's Heart'!

57:36.859 --> 57:38.770
Cheers!

57:39.061 --> 57:41.007
Good work everyone.

57:43.199 --> 57:43.904
So-yool!

57:43.966 --> 57:45.707
So-yool's here!

57:46.402 --> 57:48.382
Yoon-woo!

57:48.704 --> 57:50.411
You were amazing.

57:50.539 --> 57:54.043
Seeing the newspaper tomorrow,
I'll have a heart attack.

57:55.244 --> 57:56.314
Yeon-hee!

57:56.612 --> 57:59.616
Your whole world will change tomorrow!

58:01.250 --> 58:02.524
Min-young!

58:04.854 --> 58:06.521
Come quickly!

58:06.522 --> 58:08.331
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

58:08.390 --> 58:10.165
Applause!

58:11.393 --> 58:13.202
I forgot flowers...

58:13.395 --> 58:16.774
An encore performance from our new singer!

58:23.239 --> 58:24.775
Thank you.

58:25.307 --> 58:27.253
Thank you very much.

58:27.843 --> 58:29.823
I'd like to sing a duet.

58:31.113 --> 58:35.118
With the one person who's
happier for me than myself.

58:36.685 --> 58:37.993
So-yool!

58:39.522 --> 58:41.195
No way!

58:41.924 --> 58:45.838
Please! Go up there! Give her a big hand!

58:54.537 --> 58:55.709
What song?

58:56.605 --> 58:58.243
How about 'Spring Lady'?

59:02.278 --> 59:03.416
'Spring Lady' please.

59:04.146 --> 59:04.920
Wait.

59:04.980 --> 59:10.862
For our two beautiful ladies,
I'll shine the light!

59:11.153 --> 59:12.359
Tada!

59:24.400 --> 59:28.314
<i>♪ Spring lady ♪</i>

59:28.370 --> 59:33.479
<i>♪ Her heart is blooming ♪</i>

59:33.609 --> 59:37.345
<i>♪ Spring lady ♪</i>

59:37.346 --> 59:42.261
<i>♪ The moon sets on her ♪</i>

59:42.351 --> 59:47.061
<i>♪ Just the sound of willow pipes ♪</i>

59:51.760 --> 59:56.004
<i>♪ Spring lady's heart ♪</i>

59:56.065 --> 01:00:00.673
<i>♪ Is blooming like flowers ♪</i>

01:00:07.876 --> 01:00:15.876
<i>♪ Spring lady's ribbon ♪
♪ is pretty scarlet ♪</i>

01:00:16.752 --> 01:00:24.752
<i>♪ Spring lady's first love ♪
♪ is blossoming ♪</i>

01:00:25.761 --> 01:00:30.801
<i>♪ The sound of the stream ♪</i>

01:00:35.037 --> 01:00:39.008
<i>♪ Spring lady's heart... ♪</i>

01:01:13.542 --> 01:01:14.953
Wait!

01:01:33.329 --> 01:01:34.865
You're still here?

01:01:37.833 --> 01:01:39.107
Go home.

01:01:48.777 --> 01:01:50.381
What's with your leg?

01:01:51.080 --> 01:01:52.080
What?

01:01:52.815 --> 01:01:54.522
It's nothing.

01:01:55.718 --> 01:01:57.418
When did you hurt it?

01:01:57.419 --> 01:01:58.454
I'm fine.

01:01:58.520 --> 01:02:00.261
It doesn't hurt.

01:02:23.846 --> 01:02:27.521
<i>CACTUS FLOWER</i>

01:02:32.087 --> 01:02:33.725
It's okay.

01:02:34.590 --> 01:02:36.228
I'm fine, really.

01:02:36.291 --> 01:02:37.531
You heard!

01:02:38.227 --> 01:02:42.505
You're no longer the same SEO Yeon-hee!

01:02:42.631 --> 01:02:47.011
Why are you so mad?

01:02:48.670 --> 01:02:49.978
I'm mad!

01:02:50.139 --> 01:02:52.085
I'm angry!

01:02:53.675 --> 01:02:57.179
Why am I so angry? I just am!

01:03:56.839 --> 01:03:58.512
<i>Until now...</i>

01:03:59.074 --> 01:04:03.750
<i>I've never had anyone in my heart but you.</i>

01:04:05.981 --> 01:04:11.431
<i>2 years should do to be my bride.</i>

01:05:00.636 --> 01:05:02.240
Are you awake?

01:05:11.146 --> 01:05:13.092
So-yool! No!

01:05:18.520 --> 01:05:19.726
You...

01:05:20.789 --> 01:05:22.200
Don't worry.

01:05:22.791 --> 01:05:24.464
As you wish...

01:05:26.261 --> 01:05:28.400
I'll guard this agency.

01:05:34.269 --> 01:05:38.217
You should make at least 5,000 copies!

01:05:38.273 --> 01:05:42.153
A man should dream big!

01:05:42.210 --> 01:05:44.247
The phone is ringing off the hook!

01:05:44.313 --> 01:05:46.657
- I'm in the newspaper?
- Yes.

01:05:46.982 --> 01:05:49.984
If you wait till the permit,
you won't get enough.

